		<h1>Welcome To Battery University</h1>
		
		<p>
	Battery University&trade; offers practical battery information to engineers, educators, media, students and battery users alike. The articles address different battery chemistries, advise on best battery choice and discuss how to extend battery life.</p>
<p>
	The material is derived from the book &ldquo;Batteries in a Portable World &ndash; A Handbook on Rechargeable Batteries for Non-Engineers&rdquo; (3rd edition). For the full text we recommend you purchase &ldquo;Batteries in a Portable World.&rdquo;</p>
<p>
	Battery University&trade; is sponsored by Cadex Electronics Inc., a manufacturer of advanced battery analyzers, chargers and monitoring devices. The information is free of charge for the benefit of battery users. If you intend to use the material for education or publishing, we kindly ask you to obtain permission.</p>
<p>
	The &quot;lobby&quot; of Battery University has been made brighter, but the renovations continue. As part of publishing the 3rd edition of <b>&quot;Batteries in a Portable World,&quot;</b> we will add new material over the next few months. The book will be available in January 2011.</p>
<p>
	Enjoy your batteries,</p>
<div>
	Isidor Buchmann</div>
<div>
	CEO and Founder, Cadex Electronics Inc.</div>

		
